 to post that on an official channel just a couple of years ago? Gross.=E2=
=80=9D =E2=80=94A former ESPNer

[Ed. note: ESPN officially is not commenting on any of this.]

Regarding Comcast=E2=80=99s openness to offload its cable channels: =E2=80=
=9CWhether he was right or wrong, [former
WarnerMedia C.E.O.] Jason Kilar is the only modern media exec who=E2=80=99s=
 had the balls to try to upset the status quo and execute an ambitious visi=
on of a digital future. I=E2=80=99m not saying other execs should follow hi=
s exact model. But it is clear that these companies need to brace themselve=
s for short-term pain in order to build a bridge to the future, which no on=
e has been willing to do just yet. It will be interesting to see who bites =
the bullet first and how they position their company moving forward.=E2=80=
=9D =E2=80=94An entertainment strategist

A note on the NBA=E2=80=99s early-season rating drops: =E2=80=9CShaq isn=E2=
=80=99t wrong about the three-point shooting. It does make the game more bo=
ring to watch a team attempt 40-plus three-pointers every game. I don=E2=80=
=99t know when it=E2=80=99ll change, but I=E2=80=99d be pretty surprised if=
 I=E2=80=99m watching the NBA in 10 years and that line hasn=E2=80=99t move=
d.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94An old-school Varsity subscriber

A reflection on
Florio=E2=80=99s Varsity appearance: =E2=80=9CI agree with Mike Florio that=
 there is a number that=E2=80=99s likely been passed around the league offi=
ce to sell NFL Network games to a third party if they can find the right bu=
yer and their affiliate agreements allow them to do so. In a couple years, =
we could see the live games from both NBA TV and the NFL Network migrate to=
 streaming partners.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A Varsity subscriber

